ing memories of other tragedies triggered by this recent tragedy, please know that the Counseling Center remains available as a safe and confidential space in which to talk with a mental health counselor. Contact us at 312.996.3490 (M-F, 8a.m. – 5p.m.) or call the InTouch Hotline 312.996.5535 (Sunday thru Friday, 6 p.m. – 10:00 p.m.). Taking care of yourself by accessing available support and staying connected with others by offering your support is encouraged. For additional resources, see the link and information provided by the American Psychological Association: http://www.apa.org/helpcenter/mass-shooting.aspx      Modified on January 08, 2019                 UIC Logo        Counseling Center          Contact   UIC Counseling Center  1200 West Harrison Street, 2010 SSB, (MC 333), Chicago, Illinois 60607  Phone: (312) 996-3490  Fax: (312) 996-7645        Social Media Accounts             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 